58.0	John_Horton_Conway	John Horton Conway	John Horton Conway (born 26 December 1937) is a prolific mathematician active in the theory of finite groups, knot theory, number theory, combinatorial game theory and coding theory. He has also contributed to many branches of recreational mathematics, notably the invention of the cellular automaton called the Game of Life.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/John_H_Conway_2005_%28cropped%29.jpg/250px-John_H_Conway_2005_%28cropped%29.jpg
